ZH: 我每天上班都穿便服。
EN: I wear casual clothes to work every day.

ZH: 夏天的时候，我喜欢穿轻便服装。
EN: In summer, I like to wear light clothing.

ZH: 周末我们一家人都穿着便服。
EN: On weekends, our whole family dresses casually.

ZH: 他在家工作，所以一直穿着便服。
EN: He works from home, so he always wears casual clothes.

ZH: 我们公司规定工作日必须穿正式服装，但是周末可以穿便服。
EN: Our company requires formal attire on workdays, but casual clothes are allowed on weekends.

ZH: 这件便服很适合户外运动。
EN: This casual clothing is suitable for outdoor activities.

ZH: 她总是穿着漂亮的便服。
EN: She always wears nice casual clothes.

ZH: 我觉得穿便服更舒服。
EN: I feel more comfortable in casual clothes.

ZH: 这件便服是我最喜欢的。
EN: This casual outfit is my favorite.

ZH: 在家工作的好处之一就是可以一直穿便服。
EN: One of the advantages of working from home is being able to wear casual clothes all the time.

ZH: 去朋友家吃饭，我会穿便服，不需要太正式。
EN: When going to a friend's house for dinner, I will wear casual clothes, no need to be too formal.

ZH: 这个品牌设计的便服很时尚。
EN: The casual clothes designed by this brand are very fashionable.

ZH: 面试的时候，最好穿正式服装，不要穿便服。
EN: It is best to wear formal attire for an interview, not casual clothes.

ZH: 看电影的时候，我喜欢穿便服。
EN: I like to wear casual clothes when watching a movie.

ZH: 在家办公，我可以穿便服，不需要穿正装。
EN: I can wear casual clothes when working from home, no need for formal attire.

ZH: 人们越来越喜欢穿便服去餐馆吃饭。
EN: People are increasingly fond of wearing casual clothes to restaurants.

ZH: 周末，他们都会穿着便服去购物。
EN: On weekends, they all wear casual clothes for shopping.

ZH: 这个场合应该穿正式服装，不宜穿便服。
EN: Formal attire should be worn for this occasion, casual clothes are not appropriate.

ZH: 她工作的公司要求员工穿便服，不需要穿制服。
EN: The company she works for requires employees to wear casual clothes, no need for uniforms.

ZH: 到了夏天，我就可以换上轻便服装。
EN: When summer comes, I can switch to lightweight clothing.
